07881nam a22010815i 9783035617429DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20182022sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2018954261  a97830356174297 a10.1515/97830356174292doi  a(DE-B1597)497344  a(OCoLC)1076409412  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aDES0000002bisacsh00aNERD – New Experimental Research in Design /ced. by Michael Erlhoff, Wolfgang Jonas. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2018] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (240 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBoard of International Research in Design00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tOn Design, Research and Pudding: An Essayistic Introduction -- tSome Additional Remarks on Rigour and/or Relevance in Design Research -- tSituating Design in the Confluence of Playfulness, Ageing, and Social Transformation -- tMeans of Digital Images -- tFreedom to Make: Radical Mundanity and its Anarchic Undertones in Female Making Practice -- tFollowing the Elephant-Nosed Fish: Making Things More Complicated as a Form of Resistance -- tThe Epistemic Potential of Architectural Design: Investigating the Complex Problem of Urban Sustainability Through Spatial Practice -- tCo.Making – Design Participation in Transformation? An Experimental-Programmatic Research -- tDon’t Take out the Trash: Research Through Conceptual Designs in Design Education -- tExceptional Futures vs. Exceptions to the Future: A Pataphysical Approach to Design Fiction -- tUtopia and Uchronia: A New Experimental Approach in Thinking about Time -- tPerformative Dynamics in Designerly Economics -- tCultural Stereotypes in Letter Forms in Public Space -- tAuthors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDesign has long expressed and established itself as an independent research competence – a fact that also companies, institutions and politicians have come to acknowledge. What is still needed, however, is a stronger public platform for design to confidently reflect upon this process and to establish and communicate the specific innovative and experimental dimension of design research. For this reason, BIRD, the Board of International Research in Design, has developed the New Experimental Research in Design / NERD format. The edited conference contributions of twelve young researchers from all over the world provide an impressive and diverse and insightful range of intelligent and inspiring approaches in design research, giving rise to further debate and action in the rapidly evolving field.  aDesign hat sich lange als unabhängige Forschungskompetenz artikuliert und etabliert – eine Tatsache, die Unternehmen, Institutionen und Politiker inzwischen durchaus anerkennen. Was es noch braucht, ist eine starke öffentliche Plattform, um diesen Prozess selbstbewusst zu reflektieren und so die spezifisch innovative und experimentelle Dimension von Design-Forschung zu etablieren und kommunizieren. BIRD, das Board of International Research in Design, hat deshalb das NERD-Format entwickelt: Die hier veröffentlichten Konferenz-Beiträge von zwölf jungen Forschern aus allen Teilen der Welt geben Einblick in ein beeindruckendes und vielfältiges Spektrum von intelligenten und inspirierenden Ansätzen. Sie rufen auf zu einer Fortsetzung der Debatte in einem sich rasch entwickelnden Forschungsfeld.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aDesign-Forschung. 4aDesigner. 7aDESIGN / General.2bisacsh  a- Design Research - Designer.1 aErlhoff, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErlhoff, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGopinath, Sajith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHertrich, Susan